  <prompt>
    Build and deploy the `SummarizeFilesWizard` solution to the dev environment via the `dataverse-deploy` skill. This deploy ships the Wave 4 shared-lib migration:
    - `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` now consumes canonical `<SendEmailStep />` (task 060)
    - Inline `fetch` at line 436 removed
    - Implicit dependency on the canonical wrapper from `@spaarke/ui-components` (already published by Wave 1)

    Pre-deploy: confirm `@spaarke/ui-components` resolves to a version containing the Wave 1 wrappers + Wave 4 SummarizeFiles fix. Confirm SummarizeFilesWizard solution `npm run build` is clean.

    Post-deploy: navigate to a surface that mounts the SummarizeFilesWizard in dev. Confirm zero console errors on load. Functional smoke test is task 065.

    Note: this task is `parallel-safe: true` in `parallel-group: J` — runs in parallel with task 064 (LegalWorkspace deploy). They target different solutions, so concurrent deploys are safe at the Dataverse import layer. Both feed into smoke test 065.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Deployment engineer familiar with `dataverse-deploy` skill for SummarizeFilesWizard solution. Knows the build pipeline + solution-import path + dev environment target.
  </role>

  <goal>
    SummarizeFilesWizard solution deployed to dev with Wave 4 shared-lib changes shipped. Build clean. Lint clean. Solution imported successfully. Smoke loading shows zero console errors. Ready for task 065 (functional smoke).
  </goal>

