  <steps>
    <step order="1">Locate the SummarizeFilesWizard solution root. Likely at `src/solutions/SummarizeFilesWizard/`; if path differs, search with `ls src/solutions/` and pick the matching directory name.</step>
    <step order="2">Pre-deploy: from the solution root:
      <code>
      npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund
      npm run build
      npm run lint
      </code>
      If any step fails, escalate to task 060 — do NOT attempt deploy with broken build.
    </step>
    <step order="3">Verify `@spaarke/ui-components` resolves to a version containing the Wave 4 canonical wrapper consumption (task 060 output). Inspect `node_modules/@spaarke/ui-components/dist/` or equivalent for the migrated SummarizeFilesDialog.</step>
    <step order="4">Invoke `dataverse-deploy` skill: target = dev, solution = SummarizeFilesWizard.</step>
    <step order="5">Monitor deploy. On success: capture timestamp + dev environment URL. On failure: capture error, escalate per category (build → task 060; auth → re-authenticate).</step>
    <step order="6">Post-deploy: load the SummarizeFilesWizard surface in browser DevTools. Confirm zero console errors on load. Functional smoke is task 065 — do NOT execute send from this task.</step>
    <step order="7">Write deploy summary to `notes/wave-4-deploy-summarize.md`: timestamp, dev URL, console-check result.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 063 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (065 if 064 already complete; otherwise wait for 064).</step>
  </steps>

